               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-259-person1444">
                  RUTH 
                  SARAH ESTALL
               <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1444" type="surname" value="SARAH ESTALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1444" type="given" value="RUTH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1444" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep a lodging-house for seamen at <placeName id="t18280911-259-crimeloc1330">Bell's-wharf, Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-259-crimeloc1330" type="placeName" value="Bell's-wharf, Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-259-crimeloc1330" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-259-off1328 t18280911-259-crimeloc1330"></join>. The prisoner lodged at my house - he left me on the 29th of July, between six and seven o'clock in the evening, and did not return; I missed this property, which belonged to Bartholomew Crannell Longmuir - I had seen them safe the day before in his chest, in the back kitchen; he was at work on board a ship - this is one of his shirts; I had given it out to be washed several times.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-259-person1445">
                  CATHERINE 
                  PORTER
               <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1445" type="surname" value="PORTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1445" type="given" value="CATHERINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1445" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Dean-street, Shadwell. On Tuesday evening, the 29th of July, I saw the prisoner at near eight o'clock - he passed by and spoke to me, and I saw a quadrant in his bosom; I pulled his waistcoat aside, and saw it; I asked what he was going to do with it - he said he was going to take it to the young man it belonged to; he called him James.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-259-person1446">
                  JOSEPH 
                  HAWES
               <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1446" type="surname" value="HAWES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1446" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1446" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live in Ratcliffe-highway. On Tuesday, the 29th of July, the prisoner pawned a quadrant with me, about half-past eight o'clock in the evening; my house is about five minutes walk from Mrs. Estall's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-259-person1447">
                  EMANUEL 
                  SOLOMONS
               <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1447" type="surname" value="SOLOMONS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1447" type="given" value="EMANUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1447" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a salesman at Rosemary-lane. I bought two duplicates of the prisoner - one was for a quadrant, and the other a shirt; I got the quadrant from Mr. Hawes, and sold it to Mr. Harris; I got the shirt - this is it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-259-person1448">
                  HENRY 
                  HARRIS
               <interp inst="t18280911-259-person1448" type="surname" value="HARRIS"></interp>
